This paper discusses the security risks associated with outsourced training of deep learning models, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on the performance of neural networks, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG). The examples provided in the paper involve image classification tasks, which are typically studied in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for malicious behavior in neural networks, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SI).
